# Portable Mode / Distribution

Worlds and saves are now file-backed and manually opened, so the remaining
distribution idea is a proper portable mode.

Desired shape:

- if config/data live next to the executable, use those instead of the normal
  OS config/data dirs
- that makes it possible to hand out a zip that is basically:
  - binary
  - config next to it
  - worlds next to it
  - maybe saves next to it
- this should be a portable mode, not the only mode

That would make "easy customization" and private themed distributions much
cleaner without inventing a separate bundle format.

# World Structure

The current "character" model is still too weak for how the editor is really
used.

What is needed instead:

- world blocks: reusable chunks of description
- variants: named setups / subvariants that include some blocks and add their
  own text
- player characters: actual character descriptions / starting states

This should replace the current abuse where "characters" are often really
scenario variants.

Why this is needed:

- some chunks of description belong in many variants, but not all
- the current alternatives are both bad:
  - duplicate the same text into many sections
  - or keep it in the main description and tell the model to ignore parts of
    it in some cases

Important UX constraint:

- the data model can be more explicit, but the editor should not dump all of
  that complexity on normal users at once
- the basic editing flow should stay simple
- blocks / composition can be exposed as a more explicit advanced structure
